column5: so I don't need the baseball bat to fix that beep.......LOL...cool
great way to share a report..nothing like some good ole funning around between fishin pals
Thats only because you got alottttttttttt more to suck in pop. Oh I can feel the hit to the back of the head from here
Come on Terry.let me hit,just once.  Im sure that will fix the beep and the speacker.

What a great morning to get out for some smallie action. Well the perch were biting aswell,eh Terry. Anyhoo I felt like I was fishing with Bill Dance and his bloopers. Have a gander.   Short vid.  http://smg.photobucket.com/albums/v731/mis...ener08002-1.flv  Fish were slow and scattered. Managed a few fish,no real bigg,ns.  Making plans to head out again next weekend. Thanks again bud.
Looks like he's unwrapping his line from the trolling motor. And then he's gonna sit on his sandwich. What did I win?
LOL I was going to eat the sandwich while his back was turned.
you take a guy fishing out of the goodness of your heart and this is how they pay you back......... good fishing with you again
What are friends for. I would also like to say thanks for going out of yer way to pick me up,as my wheels were in the garage still.  Yer a good ol boy. There,does that make us even.LOL
sure it does Brian, sure............................LOL
Freakin trolling motors.....always getting in the way......don't ya hate that.....LOL .  nice fish Brian.......your looking pretty trim too I might add.......you been workin out?  Sinker
Good to see you guys smashin the bass! I have a buddy that steady gets his line in my trolling motor!!! I feel like I am the skipper and he is gilligan!!lol
some nice looking bass.
no, he hasn't  I photoshop the bass bigger and him skinnier ...........LOL
You did not. You bugger you. Thanks Sinker. Feel good too.
ok I have to do it here is the real photo sorry LOLOLOLOLOLOLOLOL LOLWROTF

Hi Terry,  We were in Cooks yesterday, it was slow to say the least and lots of dead carp, which was a bit nasty.  Which brings up my question, it looks like you were on the N. Shore, were there any dead carp on that side of the lake.  Do you think that all dead carp might have an effect on the bass and pike fishing?

no  dead carp up where we were but I here there are at pefferlaw, so it will be the whole lake soon  and yes I do think the rotting carp will slow the fishing down or maybe it will push the fish out deeper, as carp do seem to hang out in the deeper water.... another week and they are going to stink so bad, I don't think I will want to fish near them
Nice fish Brian here i thought terry was going to fall in the water you could have gave him a push lol  Rob

LOL Terry, that picture is hilarious.  I was going to say you looked slimmer B.  Good for you, is it from all the golfing you said you were going to do?  Nice report guys.  Love fishing those Simcoe Smallies  Joey
Hahah, you guys sure have fun out there don't ya
At least he didn't break the shaft again !!!!!!!
Terry..you are a riot!
LOL, you guys are too funny.  Nice fish
LOL....love that photoshopped pic.  Good friends laughing at the other's expense...gotta love it.  Oh yeah...nice fish too!!
My first thought on the pic was Terry was hiding yet another Sheepshead from the camera! I know I would! Thanks for the laugh guys! HH

Walking is good for ya,the swinging part,well,it does hurt alittle J.  Wish it did,bloody beeping drives me crazy.LOL  Thats what it,s all about.  As for the photoshop,lets just say I,ll get ya back for that one bud.LOL  Everytime I watch the vid of you,and see your reaction,I howl.LOL
nice fish brian but Iam still better looking then you I just cant suck it in as far as you can now lol lol
Oh and BTW Brian/Terry.. you can get rid of the annoying beep of the MGuide. Pop the cover and find the speaker!
